Ipsos Kenya has released findings of a national survey that focused on perception of Kenyans on graft fight. Among the highlights are perceived Magnitude of the Corruption Problem, Perceived “Most Corrupt” Present and Past Leaders, Expectations of Corruption Convictions as well as perceived justice equity when pursing ‘big’ people vs ordinary citizens. The survey was done between July 25th and August 2nd and 2,016 respondents were sampled. Again NYS, Kenya power, sugar importation, maize importation topped the list of scandals in the survey. And here are some of the public’s perception on graft fight.